+## Acceptance Reconciliation Rule
+
+When a later, narrower recovery task is accepted and validated, treat older blocked tasks for the same contract as stale supervisor state instead of active implementation work.
+
+For the current public source inventory sequence, the accepted sentinel-preserving validator task supersedes these older blocked tasks:
+
+- The original broad public source inventory validator task.
+- The sentinel-only restore task.
+- The first one-file validator retry.
+- The no-dataclass retry that still changed `validator_status()`.
+
+The supervisor must not invoke the worker on those stale blocked tasks again. If the task board still reports only blocked tasks and no selectable work, the next supervisor action should be a planning-only reconciliation that edits `ppd/daemon/task-board.md` to park or annotate the stale blocked tasks and append one narrow `[ ]` daemon-programming task that proves stale blocked tasks are ignored after a later accepted recovery.
+
+Do not edit `ppd/contracts/public_source_inventory.py` for reconciliation. The accepted implementation already passed validation.
 
