 ## Syntax-First Rule
 
 When a recent failure includes `SyntaxError`, `py_compile`, a missing import sentinel, an import-time decorator failure, or a sentinel-status assertion failure, the next proposal should be a small syntax or contract-preservation repair. Do not combine syntax recovery with contract expansion, exported API changes, or new test expectations.
+
+## Stale Blocked Count Rule
+
+Blocked task counts are diagnostic, not a reason to keep retrying obsolete work. If `progress.json` or supervisor diagnosis reports blocked tasks while the latest accepted work already validates the same recovery path, the supervisor should prefer one of these actions:
+
+1. Planning-only task-board reconciliation under `ppd/daemon/task-board.md`.
+2. A daemon-programming test under `ppd/tests/` that proves superseded blocked tasks are skipped after a later accepted task.
+3. A task-selection logic repair under `ppd/daemon/` that deprioritizes stale blocked tasks when no active `[ ]` task remains.
+
+Do not implement additional PP&D domain behavior merely to reduce the blocked count.
